example.p:
Consider the Boolean expression f\left(x_1, x_2\right) =x_1 \lor \overline{x_2} . One method of
determining the minterm normal form of f is to think in terms of sets. Consider the diagram with the usual translation of notation in . Then 

\begin{split}
f\left(x_1, x_2\right)&=\left(\overline{x_1}\land \overline{x_2}\right)\lor \left(x_1\land \overline{x_2}\right)\lor \left(x_1\land
x_2\right)\\
	& = M_{00} \lor M_{10} \lor M_{11}
\end{split}

The minterm normal form for g can be obtained by taking the join of minterms that correspond to rows that have an image value of 1. If g\left(a_1, a_2, a_3\right)=1, then include the minterm y_1\land y_2\land y_3 where
y_j=\begin{cases}
 x_j & \textrm{ if } a_j=1 \\
 \bar{x_j} & \textrm{ if } a_j=0\\
\end{cases}
Or, to use alternate notation, include M_{a_1a_2a_3} in the expression if and only if g\left(a_1, a_2, a_3\right)=1

li.p:
 Determine the minterm normal forms of



g_1\left(x_1, x_2\right)=x_1\lor x_2,


g_2\left(x_1, x_2\right)=\overline{x_1}\lor \overline{x_2}


g_3\left(x_1, x_2\right)=\overline{x_1 \land x_2}


g_4\left(x_1, x_2\right)=1
